originalText.text: Great station. Has art, bathrooms, elevator, wheelchair accessible, and clean too! Also, the E train will take you to the JFK airport. How cool is that??!! And the L to the east side of Manhattan and then to Brooklyn.

originalText.text: One of the most outfitted station stops with sculptural pieces situated along the quay platforms, made of highly polished bronze. Nearly identical to Disney-like characters it is delightfully appealing though terribly underscored over time inside the walking areas servicing both the A and C Uptown/Downtown train lines. A definite added feature that enhances the artistic imagination to the subways. Though underscored compared to within other respective stop areas.

originalText.text: Convenient station with access to the A, C, E, & L trains. One block away from the 6th & 15th station with access to the 1, 2, 3, and L tranis. There is an elevator at this station. 01/2024

originalText.text:
Attempting to get to Grand Central Terminal from 13th and Washington, I went down into the A C F line thinking it would get me there.

As I was going down the stairs onto the uptown train platform, I could not help but notice an amazing little bronze sculpture sitting on the high beams. Of course I immediately begun photographing.  Then at the bottom of the steps I saw a train guide and I asked him how long the little sculpture had bee there?

"It must be very old", I said.  "No!" he replied, 10 or 15 years. They are all over this station. Look around you, they are everywhere."

I begun to photograph...
Sculptor: Tom Otterness
Collection Title: Life Underground
Installation: 2001
Medium: Bronze
Commissioned and owned by the Metropolitan Transportation Authority "Art for Transit"

originalText.text: The A,C,E connect to the L at this station however it is a long walk from the A to the L. There are no restrooms. There is an elevator at this station and two token booth clerks at both sides of the station. There are a number of amusing statues scattered throughout the train station. A 24 hour news stand with drinks and snacks is in this station as well.
